SIMPLE: sitting
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sitting
<hw>Sit"ting</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Being in the state,
or the position, of one who, or that which, sits.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sitting</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sitting
<hw>Sit"ting</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The state or act of
one who sits; the posture of one who occupies a seat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A seat, or the space occupied by or allotted for a
person, in a church, theater, etc.; <as>as, the hall has 800
<ex>sittings</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The act or time of sitting, as to a portrait
painter, photographer, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>The actual presence or meeting of any body of men in
their seats, clothed with authority to transact business; a session;
<as>as, a <ex>sitting</ex> of the judges of the King's Bench, or of a
commission</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>sitting</qex> closed in great agitation.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>The time during which one sits while doing
something, as reading a book, playing a game, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For the understanding of any one of St. Paul's Epistles I read it
all through at one <qex>sitting</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>A brooding over eggs for hatching, as by
fowls.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The male bird . . . amuses her [the female] with his songs during
the whole time of her <qex>sitting</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sitting room</b></col>, <cd>an apartment where the
members of a family usually sit, as distinguished from a drawing-room,
parlor, chamber, or kitchen.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Situated</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Situate</ent>⟦br⟧
